1.20	Joseph_Wesbecker	Standard Gravure shooting	The Standard Gravure shooting occurred on September 14, 1989 when 47-year old Joseph T. Wesbecker, a pressman on disability for mental illness entered Standard Gravure, his former workplace, and killed eight people and injured twelve before committing suicide after a history of suicidal ideation. The murders and subsequent lawsuit against Eli Lilly &amp; Co is covered in the book The Power to Harm: Mind, Murder, and Drugs on Trial (Allen Lane and Penguin 1996) by investigative journalist John Cornwell.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/26/Joseph_Wesbecker.jpg/220px-Joseph_Wesbecker.jpg
